abstract="A major problem among the elderly are falling accidents. The newest asynchronous temporal-contrast sensors are uniquely suited for applications in this field, however, require an event-space-based approach to image processing. This paper surveys possible methods regarding their usability with this new technology. We present possible solutions for adapting existing algorithms and our new, event-space-based algorithms. We also raise some considerations regarding the reduction of false alarm rates.",
